docs.abstract: At long last, the star of the James Bond franchise bids farewell to 007 with “No Time to Die” (and learns for the first time about his life as an internet meme).
docs.snippet: At long last, the star of the James Bond franchise bids farewell to 007 with “No Time to Die” (and learns for the first time about his life as an internet meme).
docs.lead_paragraph: More than a year and a half ago, Daniel Craig and I met at the Museum of Modern Art to talk about his final James Bond movie, “No Time to Die,” and bid farewell to that suave superspy he’d been playing since 2006.

docs.abstract: Michelle Gass, the chief executive of Kohl’s, is striking deals with Amazon and Sephora in a bid to stay relevant.
docs.snippet: Michelle Gass, the chief executive of Kohl’s, is striking deals with Amazon and Sephora in a bid to stay relevant.
docs.lead_paragraph: Brick-and-mortar retailers have been decimated in recent years. First came Amazon. Then the pandemic.

headline.main: Brick-and-Mortar Retail in the Age of Covid, and Amazon
headline.print_headline: Room to Grow in Retail’s Choppy Waters

docs.abstract: The bill would curb production quotas at Amazon and other companies that critics say are excessive and force workers to forgo bathroom breaks.
docs.snippet: The bill would curb production quotas at Amazon and other companies that critics say are excessive and force workers to forgo bathroom breaks.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the latest sign of the growing scrutiny of Amazon’s labor practices, the California State Senate on Wednesday approved a bill that would place limits on production quotas for warehouse workers.

headline.main: California Senate Passes Bill Reining In Amazon Labor Model
headline.print_headline: California Senate Passes Bill Reining In Amazon’s Labor Model

docs.abstract: The tech giant has struggled to produce popular games, but a much-delayed title released this week could be the first step in a turnaround.
docs.snippet: The tech giant has struggled to produce popular games, but a much-delayed title released this week could be the first step in a turnaround.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon has been successful in nearly every industry it has entered, from books and grocery shopping to cloud computing and movie streaming. So it has been puzzling to many that success in the lucrative video game business has eluded the tech giant.

headline.main: For Flagging Amazon Games Unit, New World ‘Has to Be Our Breakthrough’
headline.print_headline: A New Try For Amazon In Gaming

docs.lead_paragraph: A lot of important words are being written about the 20th anniversary of the Sept. 11 attacks on America, marking that major and tragic turning point in history.

docs.abstract: Even for new technologies, accessibility matters.
docs.snippet: Even for new technologies, accessibility matters.
docs.lead_paragraph: Time after time, I’ve tried to use Apple’s Siri or its speech-to-text function, only for it to fail to understand my stutter.

headline.main: Voice Assistants Don’t Understand Us. They Should.
headline.print_headline: Voice Assistants Don’t Understand Us. They Should.

docs.abstract: Installment payment services are everywhere thanks to fresh deals with Amazon and Square. It’s a simple idea that can quickly get complicated for users.
docs.snippet: Installment payment services are everywhere thanks to fresh deals with Amazon and Square. It’s a simple idea that can quickly get complicated for users.
docs.lead_paragraph: That $128 pair of jeans can now be had for just four payments of $32. Dropping $100 on cosmetics seems less indulgent when the transaction is broken up into $25 payments. Even a pricey Dyson vacuum can be rationalized when purchased in $125 installments.

headline.main: Consumers and Companies Are Buying In on Paying Later
headline.print_headline: Services To Pay Later Are Soaring  In Popularity

docs.abstract: Macy’s contends the terms of its agreement with the billboard operator, Kaufman Realty, would be breached by allowing a competitor to advertise.
docs.snippet: Macy’s contends the terms of its agreement with the billboard operator, Kaufman Realty, would be breached by allowing a competitor to advertise.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the heart of Manhattan, a battle is brewing between the old-school department store Macy’s and the e-commerce giant Amazon.

headline.main: Macy’s sues to block Amazon from taking over the billboard at its Herald Square flagship.

docs.abstract: Astro has a large screen and cameras attached to a wheeled base that can navigate a home. It was part of the company’s annual devices event, where Amazon unveiled an array of product.
docs.snippet: Astro has a large screen and cameras attached to a wheeled base that can navigate a home. It was part of the company’s annual devices event, where Amazon unveiled an array of product.
docs.lead_paragraph: “Customers don’t just want Alexa on wheels,” Dave Limp, the head of Amazon’s devices, said at a company event on Tuesday. Then he proceeded to introduce a technology-packed home robot that looked a lot like … Alexa on wheels.

headline.main: Amazon announces Astro, a home robot that it swears is more than Alexa on wheels.

docs.abstract: The two women said they had been fired for speaking out. The company said they had repeatedly flouted its employee policies.
docs.snippet: The two women said they had been fired for speaking out. The company said they had repeatedly flouted its employee policies.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon has settled with two of its most prominent internal critics, staving off a public hearing over accusations that the company illegally fired the pair, lawyers for the parties told an administrative judge on Wednesday.

headline.main: Amazon settles with activist workers who say they were illegally fired.
headline.print_headline: Amazon Settles With 2 Former Employees  Who Say the Company Fired Them Illegally
